.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="842" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="84.[172,1378,825,1411]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,425,865,898]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity box="[611,705,865,898]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" unit="mm" value="54.0">54 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity box="[783,883,865,898]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 mm</quantity>
, ear 
<quantity box="[956,1054,865,898]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" unit="mm" value="29.0">29 mm</quantity>
, forearm 
<quantity box="[1197,1295,865,898]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 mm</quantity>
(type specimen). General color of the Strange Big-eared Brown Bat is dark brown, with slightly paler venter. Ears are large and connected by conspicuous membrane (¢. 
<quantity box="[1296,1378,948,977]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
high). Tragus is broad, long, and pointed at tip. Membranes and ears are dark gray.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
